HEADWORD: mammee apple
<hw>mammee apple</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A tropical
American tree (<spn>Mammea americana</spn>) having edible fruit (the
<prod>mammee apple</prod>) with a leathery rind.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mammee, mamey, mammee tree, <spn>Mammea
americana</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The globular or ovoid tropical fruit of the mammee
tree (<spn>Mammea americana</spn>), having a thick russet leathery rind
and juicy yellow or reddish flesh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mammer</ent>⟦br⟧
